v3.4.5 — Notes overhaul, spellcheck, Prosecution module

Case Notes:
- Rich-text editor (B/I/U, lists, font size, Ctrl+B/I/U)
- Image paste from clipboard + click-to-select for delete
- Spellcheck with right-click suggestions menu
- Multi-file attachments persisted under cases/{caseNumber}/Notes/
  (Field Security encryption; auto-included in DA Export ZIP)
- Inline PDF/image preview via blob: URL
- Legacy plain-text notes migrate by wrapping in <p> on first edit

Reports:
- Spellcheck enabled
- Click-to-select images for delete

App-wide:
- Right-click context menu: spelling suggestions, Add to Dictionary,
  cut/copy/paste/select-all (BrowserWindow context-menu handler)
- Menu added to electron destructure

Prosecution module - full rewrite:
- Court Case Number
- Multiple Court Dates (date/time/courtroom/type/notes)
- Court dates auto-push to dashboard task list with amber styling
- Prosecutor name/email/phone
- Charges filed from Offense Reference library OR custom typed
- Per-charge conviction tracking
- Structured sentencing (years/months incarceration, probation, notes)
- Backward-compatible migration of legacy {charge, description} array

Dashboard:
- New 'Court' task category (amber + scale icon) - distinct from priority
- getTaskColors/getTaskLabel helpers route kind:'court' tasks
